<body>
    <h1>Non =E2=80=93 Functional Requirements</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h3 id=3D"Non=E2=80=93FunctionalRequirements-1.Performance/Scalabil=
ity"><strong>1.Performance / Scalability</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Voyager IAM platform SailPoint IdentityIQ performance is expected to mat=
ch the performance benchmark set by the SailPoint vendor performance benchm=
ark considering the same level of data and other system loads.&nbsp;</p></l=
i>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Non=E2=80=93FunctionalRequirements-2.Security"><strong>2.Security=
</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Verify that SailPoint IIQ configuration settings are aligned with SailPo=
int best practices, including minimal privileges for operations and adminis=
trative tasks.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Secure connections will be established based on the capability of the sy=
stems being integrated.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Non=E2=80=93FunctionalRequirements-3.AuditandLogging"><strong>3.A=
udit and Logging</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Enable audit events logging for critical actions in the system as suppor=
ted by the SailPoint IdentityIQ platform.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Ensure audit logs include parameters supported by the SailPoint Identity=
IQ system for the actions performed.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Detailed verbose level logging for critical flows and components needs t=
o be enabled in SailPoint IdentityIQ production environments for the first =
week after production go-live. The logging will be reduced to only fetal or=
 error level for the critical components starting from the second week post=
 go-live.&nbsp;</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Non=E2=80=93FunctionalRequirements-4.ServiceNowMonitoring/Alertin=
g"><strong>4.ServiceNow Monitoring / Alerting</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>A ServiceNow ticket will be created and assigned to Ascension Health All=
iance SailPoint IIQ support team by each use-case flow when a failure is en=
countered.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Setup a ServiceNow monitoring queue for the tickets.</p></li>
</ul>
